    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-07T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-07T08:00:00-05:00" n="433"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d433">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 War Credits/651: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-07T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >March 7, 1934—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 7—9:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>102. Department’s 85, March 6, 8 p.m. Press reports from Athens published here
                    yesterday states that on March 4 Greek Government decided to deposit 27½ percent
                    of the interest on foreign loans for 1933–34; that instructions had been
                    transmitted to the Bank of Greece to transfer the necessary exchange for the
                    payment of the coupons and that while depositing a similar proportion for French
                    bondholders the Greek Government refused to entertain French claims for payment
                    in gold francs and for referring questions to arbitration.</p>
                <p>Foreign Office states orally that no British action contemplated pending receipt
                    of official confirmation from the Greek Government of above reports.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
